title: Producer Reacts to Stray Kids "Grow Up"

I'm really glad that I got to experience this song for the first time with this music video
It was very well paired. It was very well matched
It's nice seeing a music video like this and seeing a song like this from Stray Kids because it feels like a breath of fresh air
I love Stray Kids' really dark hard concepts, but even when they're not doing a dark hard concepts
They make phenomenal music and is why I have such great faith that straight kids is
Is headed for stardom that they are going to accomplish great things
I have to give a special shout out to Woojin because not only... I've criticized Woojin before
Not only did his voice blend very well with this song
His voice complimented the song. It complimented and drove the chorus in such a powerful way
I kind of wish Woojin had the entire chorus to himself
It was that good and that's all I'll say on that because I talk about Woojin I feel like way too much now
Like he's not even my favorite member and I feel like now he's gonna become my favorite member
because like I've just watched him grow and I'm really impressed with him as a musician
I think he was phenomenal here and I think he deserved way more lines
because this song really really matched his vocals really really well
I think Changbin's part was, Changbin's part was freakin' phenomenal
Now Changbin is my favorite member. I think his lyrical flow is just a masterpiece
And hearing him say such positive encouraging words, but with the same
spitfire game that he usually does is very very intriguing
It's a very interesting contrast but it works and overall this song is just it's like a very positive song
But it's inherently bittersweet because it deals with such
Trials and tribulations, and I feel like anyone who's having a tough time, who's going through dark stuff
could really appreciate this song, could really find support in the lyrics of this song
and in its tone and this song feels just it's very airy, it's very spacious
And I love the main whistle tune that they have the the main hook. That's really good too
And overall is a great Stray Kids b-side song. I still like District 9 more just because that is the title track
but this is definitely up there. This a phenomenal song
A lot of the members got to shine and I like seeing that the rappers also got to sing
I think I didn't see as much of Chan but you know I would like to see more of him in other stuff as well
but overall this was very very well done
